Active directory and domain controller.
It is microsoft's administrative central directories's database, which contains info about created user accounts, computer accounts,
groups and other objects.
It provides authorization by using kerberos protocol.
It is used to manage users and computers.
It is used to centralised and de-centeralised resources.

* create network wide rules such as requiring unique and complex passwords.
* create network wide policies such as password expiry policy
* centerlised control of security on all computers
* Automatic network printer install as soon as the PC join the domain
* restrication on usb or removable media to prevent for using to make secure company network and stops to sperad virus or malwares
* computer locks their screen after set period of time and they require password to unlock again
* employees are disabled for exisiting from the company
